===========================================
      BASH SCRIPTING - QUICK REFERENCE
===========================================

1) SYMBOLS & OPERATORS
----------------------
#      → Comment
$      → Variable expansion
=      → Assignment
==     → String compare (inside [[ ]])
-eq    → Equal (integer compare)
-ne    → Not equal (integer compare)
-lt    → Less than
-le    → Less than or equal
-gt    → Greater than
-ge    → Greater than or equal
&&     → Logical AND
||     → Logical OR
!      → Logical NOT

>      → Redirect output (overwrite)
>>     → Redirect output (append)
<      → Input redirection
|      → Pipe output

;      → Run multiple commands
&      → Run in background
()     → Subshell
{}     → Command group / expansion
[]     → Test command
[[ ]]  → Advanced test (regex, &&, ||)

$?     → Exit status of last command
*      → Wildcard (any string)
?      → Wildcard (single char)
$#     → Number of args
$@     → All args (separately)
$*     → All args (as one string)
$( )   → Command substitution
`` ` ` → Legacy command substitution

-------------------------------------------

2) FUNCTIONS
------------
# Define
function_name() {
   commands
}

# Example
greet() {
   echo "Hello, $1"
}
greet "Anil"

Special:
$1 $2 ...   → Arguments
$@          → All args
return <n>  → Return exit code

-------------------------------------------

3) COMMON BUILT-IN COMMANDS
----------------------------
echo      → Print
read      → User input
test [ ]  → Condition check
expr      → Arithmetic
let / (( )) → Arithmetic evaluation
if/then/fi → Conditional execution
case/esac → Switch case
for/while/until → Loops
break/continue → Loop control
exit      → End script
trap      → Catch signals
export    → Set environment var
shift     → Shift arguments

-------------------------------------------
EXAMPLE SCRIPT
--------------
#!/bin/bash
name="Anil"
echo "Hello $name"

if [[ $1 -gt 10 ]]; then
   echo "Value greater than 10"
else
   echo "Value less or equal to 10"
fi

for i in 1 2 3; do
   echo "Number $i"
done
-------------------------------------------

END OF CHEAT SHEET
